File written to `.board-review-temp/calibration-rebuild/deepseek-r1.md`.

**Topline verdict: DISSENT.** The design is directionally right but over-claims on three fronts: (1) the projected override reduction from ~83% to ~12% isn't supported by the firm rules alone — it depends on n=1 candidates that are gated on harness work that doesn't exist yet; (2) the 9-category shape enum is over-fitted to 12 scans and will produce misclassifications; (3) the Q9 hard floor (≤3/12) creates a circular dependency where Phase 1 can't pass without Phase 3 harness work. The design should be accepted as a Phase 1 foundation with the override-reduction target lowered to ≤5/12 and the n=1 rules moved to a Phase 1.5 deferred ledger.